		<text>
		<body>
		<pb n="1"/>
		
			<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>St Louis</placeName> <date>Jan 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 5604</date>.</p>
			<p>Dear Sir&#33;</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">The Directors of our Bnai&#45;El Congregation&#44; elected<lb/> at our last annual meeting&#44; whose names you will see by the<lb/> enclosed list&#44; have directed me to send you our subscriptions<lb/> List and to express to you their hope&#44; that you will exert<lb/> yourself in behalf of our purpose&#59; thus far we have succeeded<lb/> in getting a pretty good subscription here and if a little more<lb/> can be collected we will soon be able to go to building</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">Though there is frequently but little gained if there stands<lb/> a <sic>beautifull</sic> house dedicated to the service of God it is of<lb/> great moment for our people here.</p>
			<p>As you will have perceived during your last visit to this city and<lb/> by your editorial experience&#44; the interest which is felt or<lb/> manifested here for our religion&#44; our literature &amp;c is far below<lb/> that of any other place in proportion to its great <sic>jewish</sic><lb/> population&#44; but it is no utopian hope&#44; that if a respectable<lb/> Synagogue is soon built&#44; many who do not belong now to<lb/> any <sic>israel</sic>. Congregation will join us&#44; and so will probably the<lb/> others&#44; now inactive congregation&#44; either as a whole or as indivi<lb/>duals&#59; more interest will then be felt in our affairs and from<lb/> this a better future may be anticipated.</p>

		<pb n="2"/>
		
			<p>The lot we bought from <persName>Mr Jacobs</persName> for the Synagogue was sold<lb/> by the same far below its real value&#44; in consideration of its<lb/> purpose&#44; it has a front of 70 feet &#40;by 75 in depth&#41; its location is<lb/> central and it is our plan to erect a plain but handsome building&#44;<lb/> the cost of which shall not exceed $6000 including fixtures&#44; and<lb/> it shall at the same time have school Rooms for religious instruction.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">Any contribution&#44; small as the amount may be&#44; will therefore be<lb/> thankfully received and be of great benefit towards a speedy<lb/> accomplishment of these designs.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">I do not think of anything else that might be of interest<lb/> for you&#44; except that some of our Israelites&#44; though foremost<lb/> in contributing for the relief of the suffering emigrants<lb/> desained[&#63;] as and about <placeName>Cairo</placeName> by [&#63;]ce&#44; have made among themselves<lb/> besides this an extra collection and handed $100.00 as<lb/> a present of a Jewish society for the same purpose to the<lb/> mayor of this city.</p>
		  <p rend="indent(1)">With feelings of confidence in your zeal that will<lb/> leave this call go lost&#44; and with the assurance of<lb/> my perfect esteem and affection</p>
		  <p rend="indent(4)">Yours</p>
		  <p rend="indent(5)"><persName role="author">Isidor Bush</persName></p>
		</body>			
